org.apache.flex.abc.semantics

Class Label

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.flex.abc.semantics.Label
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Cloneable, Comparable<Label>

    public final class Label
extends Object
implements Comparable<Label>, Cloneable
    A Label represents the target of a branch instruction; it is not the ABC OP_Label instruction. Note: this class has a natural ordering that is inconsistent with equals.

      • adjustOffset

        public void adjustOffset(int base_offset)
        This Label has been inherited by a new InstructionList, so its offset must be adjusted to point to its new position within the inheriting InstructionList. (Or, the owning InstructionList's order was perturbed by a prepend() or similar ad-hoc adjustment.)
        Parameters:
        base_offset - - the amount to adjust the position. Think of the position as a displacement, and the inherting list's size as a base.
